Brighton Tide is a script to scrape the tide time information
from VisitBrighton.com and post them to Twitter.

http://richard.dallaway.com/still-loving-the-scala

RUNNING THE APP

$ mvn package appassembler:assemble
$ sh target/appassembler/bin/tidetweet

RUNNING THE SPECS TESTS

Running the Specs test in Eclipse using Scala 2.7.7 follows the pattern
outlined at https://www.assembla.com/wiki/show/scala-ide/Using_Unit_Testing_Frameworks

You need to:
 - enable Maven dependency management if it's not already
 - follow the steps "Run your specification with JUnit4 in Eclipse" at
   http://code.google.com/p/specs/wiki/RunningSpecs#Run_your_specification_with_JUnit4
